---
import {Icon} from 'astro-icon'
import {
  AnnouncementBar,
	Button,
	Container,
	CustomerQuoteSection,
	ThreeColumnTextSection,
	YouTubeEmbedSection,
  StickyTextImageSection,
  CtaCardSection
} from '@littlesticks/odyssey-theme-components';
import MapCard from "../../components/sections/heros/MapCard.astro"
import FeatureCard from "../../components/sections/heros/FeatureCard.astro"
import Layout from '../../layouts/Page.astro';
import TextAndImageHero from '../../components/sections/heros/TextAndImageHero.astro';

const seo = {
	title: 'Greenland | Sea Kayaking',
	description: 'Sea Kayaking expeditions open to sea kayaking staff',
};
---

<Layout seo={seo} >
	<TextAndImageHero reversed>
		<div slot="text-container">
			<h1>Greenland</h1>
			<p>Eleven days including paddling, hiking and camping in southeast Greenland, just below the Arctic Circle.</p>
		</div>
		<div slot="btns-container">
			<!-- <Button href="/theme/get-started" customIcon
				>Get Started <Fragment slot="icon">
          <Icon name="ic:baseline-chevron-right"/>
        </Fragment></Button
			> -->
		</div>
		<picture slot="image-container">
			<img
				src="/assets/images/home/expeditions/greenland/greenland-main-cover.png"
				alt="Greenland Cover"
				id="home-hero-image"
			/>
		</picture>
	</TextAndImageHero>
  <StickyTextImageSection>
    <div slot="text-container">
		<h2>About</h2>
		<p>
			The team will travel primarily by kayak throughout the region, camping at multiple locations along the route 
			and hiking to explore areas near campsites. The proposed routes will include visits to local villages and 
			historical sites. The total paddling distance of the expedition will vary depending on 
			local weather and ice conditions, but the trip will likely average 15 miles per day at a 3 mph pace 
			with fully loaded kayaks. Potential sights include: humpback whales, narwals, polar bears, icebergs, 
			historic Inuit sites, and more.
		</p>
		<FeatureCard
					imgSrc="/assets/images/home/expeditions/greenland/greenland-tents"
					title="Greenland Tents"
				>
		</FeatureCard>
		<br>
		<h2>Team</h2>
		<p>We selected individuals who possess the necessary physical fitness, commitment to the outdoors,
			and ability to handle the potentially challenging weather and environmental conditions possibly 
			encountered on the expedition. Training and preparedness are essential. Along with regular training trips,
			educational opportunties have been made available on chart reading, cold weather survival, and first aid.</p>
